<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"
    xml:id="entry_ællæx1" xml:lang="os">
    <form type="lemma">
        <orth>ællæx!</orth>
    </form>
    <sense>
        <def xml:lang="ru">восклицание боли, ужаса; при удвоении (%iællæx-ællæx!%i) также удивления,
            иронии и пр</def>
        <def xml:lang="en">an exclamation of pain or horror; with reduplication (%iællæx-ællæx!%i)
            also of surprise, irony etc</def>
    </sense>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>ællæx! amardta mæ!</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>аллах! он убил меня!</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>Allah! he has killed me!</q>
            </cit>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>ællæx! amardta mæ!</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>аллах! он убил меня!</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>Allah! he has killed me!</q>
            </cit>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Из <mentioned xml:lang=""
            ><lang/><w>allāh</w><gloss><q>бог</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""
                ><w>allāh-allāh</w><gloss><q>о, боже!</q></gloss></mentioned>, Распространено по
        всему мусульманскому миру. В осетинском сошло на роль междометия и в значении ‘бог’ не
        употребляется (см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_x0ycaw"/>).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>194</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">From <mentioned xml:lang=""
            ><lang/><w>allāh</w><gloss><q>God</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""
                ><w>allāh-allāh</w><gloss><q>oh God!</q></gloss></mentioned>, Widespread throughout
        the Muslim world. In Ossetic, this word has reduced to the role of interjection and is not
        used in the meaning ‘God’ (see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_x0ycaw"/>).%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>194</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
</entry>
